                <note rend="inline" type="source">867n.404Wailing Wall/76: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-08-28T00:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 28, 1929—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>230. Your 246, August 27, 3 p.m. Consular Corps at Jerusalem have informed their
                    respective governments that in spite of reiterated requests no special
                    protection has been accorded consulates and it has been impossible to secure the
                    presence of an agent of the public force at the doors of the Consulates. You
                    should urgently bring this situation to the attention of the Foreign Office and
                    you should request that suitable measures for the protection of the American
                    Consulate General be taken with the least possible delay.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
